Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_clock_transition(25.10)                        set_clock_transition(25.10)

Name
       set_clock_transition - Specifies the transition time of sequential end-
       points of the ideal clock network

Syntax
       set_clock_transition

       [-rise]

       [-fall]

       [-min]

       [-max]

       [-min |-max]

       <slew_time>

       <clock_list>

       Specifies  the  transition  time  of  sequential endpoints of the ideal
       clock network.

       This command only affects ideal clock networks, so typically it is used
       before the clock network is implemented. If no clock transition is  ex-
       plicitly  specified for an ideal clock, the system's default transition
       time (often close to 0.0) is used. For propagated  clocks,  the  calcu-
       lated  transition times are used, so you can set propagated clocks only
       after the final clock tree is constructed.

       This command only affects sequential  clock  endpoints,  typically  the
       clock  pin  of  registers in the combinational fanout of the clock. Any
       data endpoints that are also in the combinational fanout of  the  clock
       will not be affected. The software will always use the propagated tran-
       sition  times. You can consider turning off clock-source data paths un-
       til the clock tree is built or, you can use the set_ideal_network  com-
       mand for additional control.

Parameters
       <clock_list>
              Specifies  a  list of clocks only with ideal mode in the design,
              which affects the slew times on all register clock pins  in  the
              transitive   fanout   of   the   specified   clocks.   Specified
              set_clock_transition values on register clock pins in the fanout
              of a clock with propagated latency are ignored.

       -rise | -fall
              Specifies the rising or falling edge of the register clock  pins
              on which the slew time is asserted.

       -min | -max
              Specifies  the  clock  slew  time for minimum or maximum process
              corner slew time.

       <slew_time>
              Specifies the slew time (transition time) of the clock pins.

Example
              * The following commands specify a 2.0 rise slew time and a  1.0
                fall  slew  time  for  register  clock  pins  clocked by CLKA:
                set_clock_transition    -rise    2.0     [get_clocks     CLKA]
                set_clock_transition -fall 1.0 [get_clocks CLKA]

Related Information
              * report_clocks

              * set_clock_latency

              * set_clock_uncertainty

              * set_input_delay

              * set_propagated_clock

